# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Markdit — environment configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (which is git-ignored) and fill in the values.
# Only variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to the frontend by Vite.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Azure AD (Microsoft Entra ID) application (client) id used by MSAL for the
# OneNote / Loop cloud exports. Without it, Microsoft sign-in fails with
# AADSTS900144 ("the request body must contain the following parameter:
# 'client_id'"). Local-only Word (.docx) export does NOT need this.
#
# How to obtain one (free):
#   1. Go to https://entra.microsoft.com → Applications → App registrations →
#      "New registration".
#   2. Name it (e.g. "Markdit"), choose "Accounts in any organizational
#      directory and personal Microsoft accounts".
#   3. Under "Redirect URI", add a "Single-page application (SPA)" platform with
#      URI  http://localhost:1420  (and your production origin when you ship).
#   4. Copy the "Application (client) ID" from the Overview page and paste it
#      below.
#   5. Under "API permissions", add delegated Microsoft Graph permissions:
#      Notes.Create (OneNote) and Files.ReadWrite (Loop), then grant consent.
VITE_MSAL_CLIENT_ID=
